<item>
            <title>[LU-11648] Create white list for CONFIGS directory files processing</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11648</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Not all files that are stored in CONFIGS directory should be processed. For example there are &quot;.bak&quot; files which created during change_nids operation and used to store non-modified copy. Currently blacklist is used to process CONFIGS directory (&quot;.bak&quot;s are excluded), but using whitelist looks more robust.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here is example of some MDT CONFIG directory list&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
# ls /mnt/fs2mdt/CONFIGS/
lustre-client &#160; lustre-MDT0000&#160; lustre-MDT0001&#160; lustre-MDT0002&#160; lustre-MDT0003&#160; lustre-OST0000&#160; lustre-OST0001&#160; lustre-OST0002&#160; lustre-OST0003&#160; mountdata &#160; &#160; &#160; nodemap &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; params &#160; &#160; &#160;
  sptlrpc &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;params, node map, mountdata, &lt;b&gt;client, *-MDT&lt;/b&gt;, &lt;b&gt;-OST&lt;/b&gt; sptlrpc are allowed. What else?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
